The paper deals with steganography in IP telephony, which involves network security and multimedia communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves transcoding of voice streams, which falls under the category of multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. The paper also involves compression and transmission of data, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. The paper deals with communication over IP networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the implementation of a proof of concept, which falls under the category of software development, making cs.SD (Software Engineering) a possible category as well.
